      "id": "bug-010",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-26T19:15:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Error submitting single execution: [object Response] / status 500 on POST /v1/executionEngines/tapis (Tapis job UUID returned, then opaque 500)",
      "file": "mint-ensemble-manager/src/classes/tapis/adapters/TapisJobSubscriptionService.ts, mint-ensemble-manager/src/classes/tapis/adapters/TapisExecutionService.ts",
      "root_cause": "After submitJob succeeded (UUID logged), submitSingleExecution called subscriptionsClient.subscribe directly without errorDecoder. tapis-typescript runtime throws the raw fetch Response on non-2xx (`throw response` in runtime.ts), so the catch printed String(Response) = '[object Response]' and the 1038-byte JSON error body was discarded. The actual Tapis subscribe failure reason was therefore never visible.",
      "fix": "Wrapped subscriptionsClient.subscribe(...) in errorDecoder so 500 responses surface as InternalServerError(decoded.message). Added a console.log before subscribe (jobUuid + delivery target URL) and a console.error inside the catch with the decoded message. Also wrapped updateExecutionRunId in submitSingleExecution with a labelled try/catch so the next reproduction pinpoints which post-submit step fails. Build green, tapis adapter tests 6/6 pass.",
      "tags": [
        "tapis",
        "ensemble-manager",
        "subscribe",
        "error-decoding",
        "observability",
        "500"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [
        "bug-009"
      ],
