    {
      "id": "bug-012",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-26T20:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "JOBSAPI_SUBSCRIPTION_ERROR / NTFLIB_DLVRY_ADDR_NOT_URL Delivery target address in subscription not a valid URL. Address: http://ensemble-manager.mint.local/v1/tapis/threads/.../webhook",
      "file": "mint-ensemble-manager/src/classes/tapis/adapters/TapisJobSubscriptionService.ts, mint-ensemble-manager/src/classes/mint/mint-types.ts, helm-charts/charts/mint/templates/ensemble-manager-config.yaml, helm-charts/dynamo-values.yaml",
      "root_cause": "TapisJobSubscriptionService.generateWebHookUrl built the webhook URL from prefs.ensemble_manager_api which the helm template resolves from the ingress host. In dev that host is ensemble-manager.mint.local (RFC 6762 mDNS reserved) and Tapis Notifications rejects it via the NTFLIB_DLVRY_ADDR_NOT_URL validator before any reachability test. Even if it passed, Tapis runs at portals.tapis.io and cannot resolve .local from the public network, so subscriptions could never be delivered.",
      "fix": "Decoupled webhook target from ensemble_manager_api. Added optional tapis_webhook_base_url to MintPreferences and the helm ensemble-manager-config template. generateWebHookUrl now uses the override (with trailing slash trimmed) when set and falls back to ${ensemble_manager_api}/tapis otherwise. Dev cluster (dynamo-values.yaml) points at https://webhook.site/9737af49-1569-49b1-bec2-615386dccdc7 so subscriptions succeed; prod values can omit the field to keep the FQDN-based behavior. New unit tests in TapisJobSubscriptionService.test.ts cover fallback, override, and trailing-slash trimming. npm run build passes; tapis test suites green (10/10).",
      "tags": [
        "tapis",
        "ensemble-manager",
        "subscribe",
        "webhook",
        "config",
        "helm",
        "ntflib",
        "url-validation"
