      "id": "bug-12-05-junction-array-wrap",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-28T20:11:00Z",
      "error_message": "isOptional checkbox always shows checked after page refresh, even when modelcatalog_configuration_input.is_optional=false in DB",
      "file": "model-catalog-api/src/mappers/response.ts",
      "root_cause": "Junction column hoist (commit 9bcbecd) wrapped the scalar in a single-element array (out[snakeToCamel(colName)] = [val]), mirroring v1.8.0's array-wrapped object property convention. That convention is for relationships/objects. is_optional is a plain bool. UI render does !!(r as any).isOptional. Any array (including [false]) is truthy in JS, so !![false] === true and the checkbox always renders checked.",
      "fix": "Emit out[snakeToCamel(colName)] = val (scalar) at response.ts:115. Added response.test.ts assertions for false/true scalar emission and null omission. SDK FromJSONTyped monkey-patch already handles scalars correctly.",
