      "file": "ui/src/screens/models/configure/resources/dataset-specification.ts",
      "root_cause": "ModelCatalogResource.setResources() in resource.ts:1419-1473 calls resourceApi.get(id) per row, storing the per-id GET response in _loadedResources[id]. Render (resource.ts:479,513) and getResources() (resource.ts:1642) both read from _loadedResources, NOT from the inline _resources array passed in. For DatasetSpecification, GET /datasetspecifications/{id} returns the entity scalars only — isOptional lives on the modelcatalog_configuration_input junction (configuration<->dspec binding) and is hoisted only by the parent GET /modelconfigurations/{id} response mapper. The lazy refetch wipes isOptional from the row used by render+save.",
      "fix": "In ModelCatalogDatasetSpecification, override setResources() to capture inline isOptional per-id into a _junctionOverlay map, override requestUpdate() to merge the overlay onto _loadedResources[id] when the entity GET resolves with isOptional undefined, and update the checkbox @change handler to keep _junctionOverlay in sync with user toggles.",
